				\begin{document}$$i$$\end{document} at most once at the intermediate stations.
To ensure the safety of trains, the departure and arrival times of any two trains will not be the same the two trains are not coming on the same track in the opposite direction.
Overtaking is permitted only at the stations.
Trains do not have a permanent stop at any intermediate stations until they reach their destination.
All the stations have sufficient platforms for all trains.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
